<br>
&quot;Awake.  Awake, priestess.  I would speak with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn's eyes snapped open, and she found herself staring into the face of a woman, small of stature but regal none-the-less.  Her skin was ebony, and her face surrounded by silver hair.  Two long locks ran on either side of her face, ending at her waist.  The woman held a staff, a peculiar staff, with a headpiece made of two hands holding a shimmering orb between them.  When Kerridwynn's eyes opened, the woman stepped back, the shadows swirling around her feet following the movement.  The priestess looked upon the goddess, for godess she was, but said nothing for a time.  Finally, she spoke again.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Startled you, did I?  I imagine so, you were dead to the world.  You've the look of someone who does not sleep easily under any circumstance, and sorry I was to waken you, but we must speak, you and I.  Aye, we must speak.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The voice was quiet, the tone melodical but deep.  Kerridwynn only nodded once, as if to say &quot;You woke me, so out with it then.&quot;  The goddess nodded herself, and hunkered down over her feet, graceful as a cat.  The shadows about her feet ducked and swirled.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;I've watched you, priestess, for a very long time.  In fact, I've been at work in your life for the entire time you've drawn breath, although you were never aware of it.  It pleased me to remain in the shadows.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The goddess laughed, as if she's shared a joke.  And perhaps she had.  Kerridwynn looked down at the shadows swirling about the woman's feet, and smiled slightly.  The woman grinned and went on.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;If you know your pantheon, and I know you do, as you are a priestess and born to know the gods and goddesses, in all of their guises, then you know who I am.  I will not bore you by telling you what you already know.  But I will tell you that the time has come for you to serve me in name, as well as in deed.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn's eyes widened, and her lips parted.  She served the Father, and had since that dreadful day when Sarhea defeated the Blood, driving it from the priestess with blades and Hatred.  The goddess raised her hand, stalling the priestess' words in her throat.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Don't give me that tripe about serving the Father.  You and I know full-well that Innoruuk does not hold sway in your heart, and has never.  He may sometimes hold sway in your mind, but never for long.  Your heart...your soul...belongs to me.  You were born to the shadows, and you have walked in them your entire life.  You are mine, Kerridwynn.  *I* Named you, not Innoruuk.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The priestess closed her mouth, setting it in a firm line.  The goddess looked at her and shook her head.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Proof, eh?  It is always that way with you.  You want proof?  Fine, you shall have it.  Do you remember the night you stole away from the Temple of Innoruuk and made your way to your father's house?  Do you remember walking his halls, and how easy it was to hide in the shadows as you made your way to his bedchamber?  I can see that you do.  Do you remember the way the shadows fell upon his face, giving it the appearance of a skull?  You took that as an omen, and you killed him.  And I helped you do it.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn's eyes closed, and she took a deep breath.  When she opened them, the goddess smiled softly, and went on.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Do you remember that fateful defense of Neriak, when you finally saw the true face of your evil bretheren?  You moved your hall to Shadowhaven after that, renouncing Neriak and all it stood for.  You moved your family onto the moon named after me, Kerridwynn.  And I put the idea in your head.  You've always felt more comfortable on the moon, haven't you?  Your home.  *MY* home.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn nodded, her eyes clouded.  The goddess laid a hand on the priestess' knee.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;You are mine, priestess.  I claimed you at birth, and I have watched over you since.  Now, it is time that you know and take up my banner.  Your power springs from me, and from within yourself.  I am the Maiden of Shadows, and you are my priestess.  Do you understand?  More importantly, will you comply?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>For a time the office was silent but for the crackling of the fire.  Neither woman moved, as they stared into eachother's eyes.  Finally, Kerridwynn blinked, and slowly nodded.  The goddess smiled broadly.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Good!  Now the real fun begins.  Come, m'dear.  Tis time for your induction into my service.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The goddess stood, and offered her hand to the priestess.  Kerridwynn took it, and the office disappeared into shadow.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> <p><center><img src="http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/Kerridwynn.jpg"><BR><i>~*Vicar of Innoruuk*~<br>~*Mistress of the Scythe*~</i><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness>Harvesters of Darkness</a><br>~~~~~~~~~~<BR><i>Shattered visage, and broken heart,<br>Screams carrying in the dark.<br>Is there solace to be had?<br>Is there escape for the mad?</i><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=208851>Garb of the Priestess</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chaeslcassiline@harvestersofdarkness>Chaes LCassiline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(8/8/03 5:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fharvestersofdarknessfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shadowmistress</span><hr size=1> (( Lemme just be the first to say..BRAVO! BRAVO! *applaud!* I need to take lessons from the Grandmistress of Writing that is you. *nodnodnod* *grin* Sorry, I'm sucking up a little. Oh well. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I want lessons! )) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khorneonabrassthrone>khorne on a brass throne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(8/9/03 4:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub